WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.830 align:middle line:90%


00:00:12.830 --> 00:00:14.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hello and welcome.

00:00:14.380 --> 00:00:15.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:18.640 align:middle line:84%
Today we're going to be asking
the deeper questions: how

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:24.694 align:middle line:84%
our understanding of mind, time,
space, and matter have changed.

00:00:24.694 --> 00:00:26.110 align:middle line:84%
And we're also
going to be looking

00:00:26.110 --> 00:00:30.100 align:middle line:84%
at the art of cheating time,
otherwise known as time travel.

00:00:30.100 --> 00:00:31.740 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
look at all of this

00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:34.120 align:middle line:84%
in the perspective
of quantum physics,

00:00:34.120 --> 00:00:35.620 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to
find out how this

00:00:35.620 --> 00:00:38.240 align:middle line:84%
applies to our own
personal lives.

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:40.690 align:middle line:84%
Joining me is quantum
physicist Fred Allan

00:00:40.690 --> 00:00:43.320 align:middle line:84%
Wolf, also known
as a Dr. Quantum

00:00:43.320 --> 00:00:45.410 align:middle line:84%
as he's affectionately
called, and he

00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:48.710 align:middle line:84%
is a way of taking
these abstract topics

00:00:48.710 --> 00:00:51.490 align:middle line:84%
and really bringing them to
a simple way of understanding

00:00:51.490 --> 00:00:52.040 align:middle line:90%
them.

00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:55.079 align:middle line:84%
His latest book is called
"Time Loops and Space Twists,"

00:00:55.079 --> 00:00:57.370 align:middle line:84%
and this is what we're going
to be talking about today.

00:00:57.370 --> 00:00:58.367 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:00:58.367 --> 00:01:00.450 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED ALLAN WOLF: Thank
you very much, very much.

00:01:00.450 --> 00:01:01.540 align:middle line:90%
Nice to be here Lisa.

00:01:01.540 --> 00:01:03.415 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm glad you're
here because we are--

00:01:03.415 --> 00:01:06.530 align:middle line:84%
I'm in for a whole education
today as well as our listeners.

00:01:06.530 --> 00:01:10.462 align:middle line:84%
How long have you been
practicing quantum physics?

00:01:10.462 --> 00:01:11.420 align:middle line:90%
How do you practice it?

00:01:11.420 --> 00:01:13.020 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, as
I said, you need

00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:17.010 align:middle line:84%
to practice it because basically
practicing quantum physics

00:01:17.010 --> 00:01:19.440 align:middle line:84%
is just practicing
one basic thing

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:22.030 align:middle line:84%
we all know, do unto
others as you want them

00:01:22.030 --> 00:01:24.440 align:middle line:84%
to do onto you because
if you don't, they well.

00:01:24.440 --> 00:01:27.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that's basically
the quantum entanglement where

00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:28.370 align:middle line:90%
we're constantly--

00:01:28.370 --> 00:01:29.120 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's it.

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:32.020 align:middle line:84%
We're all basically entangled
from the Big Bang onwards,

00:01:32.020 --> 00:01:34.650 align:middle line:84%
and if what we're
talking about now

00:01:34.650 --> 00:01:37.550 align:middle line:84%
and the new ideas
of physics are true,

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:39.390 align:middle line:84%
we're entangled
from the future too.

00:01:39.390 --> 00:01:41.470 align:middle line:84%
So it's just the
future and the present

00:01:41.470 --> 00:01:45.850 align:middle line:84%
and the past are constantly
making us come into being.

00:01:45.850 --> 00:01:47.930 align:middle line:90%
So yes, we have free will.

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:49.430 align:middle line:90%
No, we don't have free will.

00:01:49.430 --> 00:01:50.180 align:middle line:90%
Yes we do.

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:51.160 align:middle line:90%
No we don't.

00:01:51.160 --> 00:01:54.270 align:middle line:84%
On a much larger
scale, it's much more

00:01:54.270 --> 00:01:57.174 align:middle line:84%
of a magical light show than
we ever, ever thought possible.

00:01:57.174 --> 00:01:59.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And what I really
appreciate about you

00:01:59.090 --> 00:02:02.190 align:middle line:84%
is you take these
complex subjects

00:02:02.190 --> 00:02:04.090 align:middle line:90%
and you bring them to reality.

00:02:04.090 --> 00:02:07.500 align:middle line:84%
You make them easy for us
to understand who are not

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:09.440 align:middle line:84%
quantum physicist,
but yet we live

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:11.800 align:middle line:84%
in the quantum world
every waking moment,

00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:13.090 align:middle line:90%
every sleeping moment.

00:02:13.090 --> 00:02:15.110 align:middle line:84%
So we are now going to
be able to understand

00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:17.900 align:middle line:84%
what this time, space, and
matter is around us right now.

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:20.880 align:middle line:84%
So right now we're
living with matter

00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:22.347 align:middle line:90%
all around us, all around us.

00:02:22.347 --> 00:02:23.180 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:26.110 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, I'll
tell you the secret

00:02:26.110 --> 00:02:28.960 align:middle line:84%
is that if there wasn't
all this stuff, matter,

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:33.080 align:middle line:84%
all the way around us, everybody
would be able to do everything

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:37.260 align:middle line:84%
they wanted instantly, and
it would be effortless,

00:02:37.260 --> 00:02:39.353 align:middle line:84%
and everything would
be, oh, wonderful.

00:02:39.353 --> 00:02:40.360 align:middle line:90%


00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:44.170 align:middle line:84%
For four days that's great,
but after an eternity of that,

00:02:44.170 --> 00:02:45.545 align:middle line:90%
it's boring, boring.

00:02:45.545 --> 00:02:46.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:02:46.170 --> 00:02:47.620 align:middle line:90%
That sounds pretty good to me.

00:02:47.620 --> 00:02:48.830 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Try it.

00:02:48.830 --> 00:02:51.100 align:middle line:84%
If you get everything
you want, everything you

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:52.414 align:middle line:90%
want all the time--

00:02:52.414 --> 00:02:53.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Then you'd
be a celebrity.

00:02:53.830 --> 00:02:56.587 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: --then you actually
don't want anything,

00:02:56.587 --> 00:02:58.170 align:middle line:84%
because you've got
everything, so what

00:02:58.170 --> 00:02:59.140 align:middle line:90%
are you going to do now?

00:02:59.140 --> 00:03:01.090 align:middle line:84%
Well, you want something
that's going to challenge you,

00:03:01.090 --> 00:03:02.950 align:middle line:84%
something that's
going to inspire you,

00:03:02.950 --> 00:03:06.570 align:middle line:84%
something that you're going to
have to work towards getting.

00:03:06.570 --> 00:03:09.870 align:middle line:84%
And that's where you
might say God had this--

00:03:09.870 --> 00:03:10.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Plan.

00:03:10.550 --> 00:03:12.000 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Great thought.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.860 align:middle line:84%
Let's make a material
world in which

00:03:14.860 --> 00:03:17.240 align:middle line:84%
people don't get exactly
what they want instantly.

00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:20.250 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I'm going to get
into this world in such a way

00:03:20.250 --> 00:03:22.880 align:middle line:84%
that even I don't get
what I want instantly

00:03:22.880 --> 00:03:25.290 align:middle line:84%
because I'm going to
forget who I really am.

00:03:25.290 --> 00:03:29.495 align:middle line:84%
And when I did that, suddenly
I appeared as Lisa Garr.

00:03:29.495 --> 00:03:30.890 align:middle line:90%


00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:33.110 align:middle line:90%
There she is, god in person.

00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:35.820 align:middle line:84%
Fred Alan Wolf, there
he is, god in person.

00:03:35.820 --> 00:03:39.120 align:middle line:84%
And every other of the 7
billion or how many people

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:42.110 align:middle line:84%
we have on the planet now,
they're all god in disguise,

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:45.170 align:middle line:84%
none of them realizing that the
reason they're in a material

00:03:45.170 --> 00:03:50.680 align:middle line:84%
body is because they want to
be able to achieve something

00:03:50.680 --> 00:03:53.550 align:middle line:84%
in their life other
than just living.

00:03:53.550 --> 00:03:55.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So is it
more than the mind

00:03:55.140 --> 00:03:57.060 align:middle line:84%
and the ego that
wants to achieve?

00:03:57.060 --> 00:04:02.290 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: It's kind
of a cosmic game.

00:04:02.290 --> 00:04:06.040 align:middle line:84%
The game is I want
to achieve, but I

00:04:06.040 --> 00:04:09.366 align:middle line:84%
don't want to make
it so easy to achieve

00:04:09.366 --> 00:04:12.667 align:middle line:84%
that I have no sense
of accomplishment.

00:04:12.667 --> 00:04:14.625 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that's really
a law in the universe.

00:04:14.625 --> 00:04:16.370 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: It is a law
in the universe.

00:04:16.370 --> 00:04:21.920 align:middle line:84%
The basic law of the universe
is to forget yourself, remember

00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:22.520 align:middle line:90%
yourself.

00:04:22.520 --> 00:04:24.785 align:middle line:84%
To remember yourself,
forget yourself.

00:04:24.785 --> 00:04:25.820 align:middle line:90%


00:04:25.820 --> 00:04:29.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, in all the spiritual
teachings, they all say this,

00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:31.640 align:middle line:84%
and everybody says, what
the heck you talking about?

00:04:31.640 --> 00:04:33.480 align:middle line:84%
And from a quantum
physics point of view,

00:04:33.480 --> 00:04:36.510 align:middle line:84%
it makes perfectly good
sense as we will find out,

00:04:36.510 --> 00:04:39.350 align:middle line:84%
as we explore in the show
we're doing together.

00:04:39.350 --> 00:04:40.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:04:40.120 --> 00:04:40.620 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:04:40.620 --> 00:04:41.578 align:middle line:90%
So let's get into this.

00:04:41.578 --> 00:04:42.650 align:middle line:90%
So what does it mean?

00:04:42.650 --> 00:04:44.325 align:middle line:90%
Is it really all an illusion?

00:04:44.325 --> 00:04:46.360 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, that
is a good question.

00:04:46.360 --> 00:04:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Is it really all an illusion,
or is it not all an illusion?

00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:52.370 align:middle line:84%
Well, in order to
get into that, we

00:04:52.370 --> 00:04:57.510 align:middle line:84%
need to talk about not
only is it an illusion,

00:04:57.510 --> 00:05:01.670 align:middle line:90%
but who's fooling who with what?

00:05:01.670 --> 00:05:06.330 align:middle line:84%
What is the illusion consisting
of, and who's the illusion for?

00:05:06.330 --> 00:05:10.640 align:middle line:84%
You know, when a magician does
a trick, there's an audience

00:05:10.640 --> 00:05:12.050 align:middle line:90%
and there's a performer.

00:05:12.050 --> 00:05:15.389 align:middle line:84%
And the performer is doing
the trick for the audience.

00:05:15.389 --> 00:05:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's observing
the performer.

00:05:16.930 --> 00:05:19.720 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Now, think of what
you might do with that if you

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:24.540 align:middle line:84%
are the performer and the
audience at the same time.

00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:26.290 align:middle line:84%
Then you're doing it
in front of a mirror,

00:05:26.290 --> 00:05:32.520 align:middle line:84%
and it turns out that mirrors
and mirror symmetries are

00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:36.210 align:middle line:84%
the most important thing we have
discovered in quantum physics

00:05:36.210 --> 00:05:37.210 align:middle line:90%
to date.

00:05:37.210 --> 00:05:39.350 align:middle line:84%
It helps us to
understand, actually,

00:05:39.350 --> 00:05:41.690 align:middle line:84%
how this universe got
created in the first place,

00:05:41.690 --> 00:05:44.190 align:middle line:84%
and even how time and
matter get created.

00:05:44.190 --> 00:05:46.270 align:middle line:84%
It's all really
done with mirrors,

00:05:46.270 --> 00:05:48.390 align:middle line:84%
and that's something we
are going to explore.

00:05:48.390 --> 00:05:49.870 align:middle line:90%
So is it all an illusion?

00:05:49.870 --> 00:05:50.860 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it is.

00:05:50.860 --> 00:05:52.000 align:middle line:90%
It basically is.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:54.570 align:middle line:84%
And what we're going
to find out is,

00:05:54.570 --> 00:05:56.410 align:middle line:84%
what's making the
illusion come in?

00:05:56.410 --> 00:05:58.120 align:middle line:90%
Who is the illusion for?

00:05:58.120 --> 00:05:59.500 align:middle line:90%
It's God.

00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:00.800 align:middle line:90%
It's the mind of God.

00:06:00.800 --> 00:06:01.490 align:middle line:90%
It's your mind.

00:06:01.490 --> 00:06:02.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Explain the mind of God.

00:06:02.740 --> 00:06:04.590 align:middle line:84%
We're not talking about
the white man in the sky.

00:06:04.590 --> 00:06:05.090 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:07.160 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about
from a universal God.

00:06:07.160 --> 00:06:07.890 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:06:07.890 --> 00:06:12.560 align:middle line:84%
From a certain perspective, from
a quantum physical, scientific

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.610 align:middle line:84%
kind of perspective,
which by the way,

00:06:14.610 --> 00:06:16.380 align:middle line:90%
no scientist would ever say.

00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:20.310 align:middle line:84%
Because scientists live
under the Shibboleth thou

00:06:20.310 --> 00:06:24.270 align:middle line:84%
shalt not ever mention
spiritual or God or religion

00:06:24.270 --> 00:06:26.774 align:middle line:84%
or spirituality
because it's forbidden.

00:06:26.774 --> 00:06:28.190 align:middle line:84%
And the reason
we're doing this is

00:06:28.190 --> 00:06:30.610 align:middle line:84%
because 500 years ago,
you were chopping off

00:06:30.610 --> 00:06:32.820 align:middle line:84%
the heads of scientists,
you religious guys,

00:06:32.820 --> 00:06:34.910 align:middle line:84%
and we don't want you to
do that anymore to us.

00:06:34.910 --> 00:06:35.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:36.000 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:36.916 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: They remember.

00:06:36.916 --> 00:06:37.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:06:37.710 --> 00:06:39.460 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: You don't
forget things like that.

00:06:39.460 --> 00:06:42.800 align:middle line:84%
So science has been
anti-religious ever since.

00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:46.990 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, the mind
of God is a field

00:06:46.990 --> 00:06:48.800 align:middle line:90%
which fills the whole universe.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.030 align:middle line:90%


00:06:50.030 --> 00:06:54.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's your mind, and when
you remember who you really are,

00:06:54.830 --> 00:06:59.070 align:middle line:84%
you identify with this field,
which is the mind of God.

00:06:59.070 --> 00:07:02.020 align:middle line:84%
And from that point
of view, you project

00:07:02.020 --> 00:07:06.150 align:middle line:84%
into various activities,
universes, worlds,

00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:07.940 align:middle line:84%
however you want
to play the game.

00:07:07.940 --> 00:07:10.930 align:middle line:84%
And as long as you remember
who and what you are,

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.510 align:middle line:84%
you could always get out as
well as get back in again.

00:07:14.510 --> 00:07:18.832 align:middle line:84%
For those of us living here
on Earth, our 80 to 100

00:07:18.832 --> 00:07:20.890 align:middle line:84%
or 90 to 1,000,
whatever years we're

00:07:20.890 --> 00:07:23.420 align:middle line:84%
going to be alive on
this planet-- for us,

00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:26.380 align:middle line:84%
for ordinary folk,
we kind of forget it

00:07:26.380 --> 00:07:29.890 align:middle line:84%
because we get so much
into the day-to-day stuff

00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:30.760 align:middle line:90%
that we forget that.

00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:36.622 align:middle line:84%
So we give ourselves a
gentle reminder, we die.

00:07:36.622 --> 00:07:37.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Gentle.

00:07:37.620 --> 00:07:38.730 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Very gentle.

00:07:38.730 --> 00:07:40.630 align:middle line:84%
We just get out of
here after a while,

00:07:40.630 --> 00:07:43.970 align:middle line:84%
because you get too attached
it, and sometimes life

00:07:43.970 --> 00:07:45.817 align:middle line:84%
can be hard because,
after all, you

00:07:45.817 --> 00:07:47.150 align:middle line:90%
are trying to move around mass--

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:50.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But as I've heard,
that when you do crossover,

00:07:50.170 --> 00:07:52.590 align:middle line:84%
from many of the guests who
have sat in this chair here,

00:07:52.590 --> 00:07:55.970 align:middle line:84%
that idea of the quantum
field then expands,

00:07:55.970 --> 00:07:57.760 align:middle line:84%
and that's the
place to live from.

00:07:57.760 --> 00:08:00.160 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: You know,
expands, contracts,

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:03.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, whatever it does,
you're already there.

00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:05.670 align:middle line:84%
The point is that when
you're in body form,

00:08:05.670 --> 00:08:08.070 align:middle line:84%
you don't know
you're there or you

00:08:08.070 --> 00:08:11.110 align:middle line:84%
tend to forget you're there
because the ego, which

00:08:11.110 --> 00:08:15.700 align:middle line:84%
is the body-mind, which is
that mind which is telling you,

00:08:15.700 --> 00:08:17.770 align:middle line:84%
don't stick your finger
in the white socket.

00:08:17.770 --> 00:08:19.356 align:middle line:90%


00:08:19.356 --> 00:08:20.260 align:middle line:90%
Ah, the light's red.

00:08:20.260 --> 00:08:20.780 align:middle line:90%
Don't cross.

00:08:20.780 --> 00:08:21.340 align:middle line:90%
Don't cross.

00:08:21.340 --> 00:08:22.180 align:middle line:90%
Don't cross.

00:08:22.180 --> 00:08:24.550 align:middle line:84%
That mind, that
body-mind is more--

00:08:24.550 --> 00:08:27.540 align:middle line:84%
it's concerned with the
survival of the mind

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:29.030 align:middle line:90%
within the framework.

00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:31.100 align:middle line:84%
The confusion that
comes from that

00:08:31.100 --> 00:08:34.450 align:middle line:84%
is that, ah, that's
all that it is.

00:08:34.450 --> 00:08:42.650 align:middle line:84%
My mind is some kind of
emergence from the body,

00:08:42.650 --> 00:08:47.280 align:middle line:84%
and the body-- you're born,
terrible; you live, terrible;

00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:48.276 align:middle line:90%
you die, black.

00:08:48.276 --> 00:08:49.554 align:middle line:90%


00:08:49.554 --> 00:08:51.633 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That would be horrible.

00:08:51.633 --> 00:08:54.010 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: That's basically
the way people think,

00:08:54.010 --> 00:08:57.040 align:middle line:90%
and that is-- some people think.

00:08:57.040 --> 00:09:02.120 align:middle line:84%
And that is not only
unpleasant, but it's basically

00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:03.610 align:middle line:90%
an assumption.

00:09:03.610 --> 00:09:06.090 align:middle line:90%
It's not a basic truth.

00:09:06.090 --> 00:09:09.850 align:middle line:84%
It's not based upon anything
other than our observations

00:09:09.850 --> 00:09:12.980 align:middle line:84%
that we are born,
we live, and we die.

00:09:12.980 --> 00:09:15.480 align:middle line:84%
And that doesn't mean that
we don't continue in some way

00:09:15.480 --> 00:09:16.610 align:middle line:90%
afterwards.

00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:17.790 align:middle line:90%
We have no proof of that.

00:09:17.790 --> 00:09:19.248 align:middle line:84%
We have no way of
identifying that.

00:09:19.248 --> 00:09:21.570 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm trying
to do is explain

00:09:21.570 --> 00:09:23.930 align:middle line:84%
that there has to be mind
present in the universe,

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:27.960 align:middle line:84%
and that means that the
present state of that mind

00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:30.745 align:middle line:84%
in various bodies is capable
of transforming or changing.

00:09:30.745 --> 00:09:32.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what
we're doing today

00:09:32.120 --> 00:09:34.560 align:middle line:84%
is we're going to go on this
journey of quantum physics

00:09:34.560 --> 00:09:37.944 align:middle line:84%
and how it relates to our
matter in time and space

00:09:37.944 --> 00:09:38.610 align:middle line:90%
in the universe.

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:41.540 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
that a little bit.

00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:45.050 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, so-- my favorite
characters as I grew up,

00:09:45.050 --> 00:09:48.130 align:middle line:84%
and I understand some of
you at home watching this

00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:49.970 align:middle line:84%
may not remember
these characters,

00:09:49.970 --> 00:09:51.585 align:middle line:90%
are the Marx brothers.

00:09:51.585 --> 00:09:53.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I remember
the Marx brothers.

00:09:53.250 --> 00:09:55.050 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And they
were very comical

00:09:55.050 --> 00:09:57.975 align:middle line:84%
because they were always trying
to figure out what to do.

00:09:57.975 --> 00:10:00.100 align:middle line:84%
They always had lots of
ideas, and they were always

00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:03.910 align:middle line:84%
come up with comical
solutions to what goes on.

00:10:03.910 --> 00:10:06.322 align:middle line:84%
Harpo was my favorite character
because he didn't speak,

00:10:06.322 --> 00:10:07.780 align:middle line:84%
but he was, I
thought, the funniest

00:10:07.780 --> 00:10:09.660 align:middle line:84%
although Groucho
was certainly funny.

00:10:09.660 --> 00:10:11.520 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, these are
the characters,

00:10:11.520 --> 00:10:13.670 align:middle line:84%
and what they were
coming up with,

00:10:13.670 --> 00:10:16.110 align:middle line:84%
you might think were
bubbles of possibilities.

00:10:16.110 --> 00:10:18.180 align:middle line:84%
And I want to play with
that idea of bubbles

00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:20.750 align:middle line:84%
of possibilities a little bit
in explaining this when we talk

00:10:20.750 --> 00:10:23.850 align:middle line:84%
about the time and
mind and quantum

00:10:23.850 --> 00:10:26.470 align:middle line:84%
bubbles of possibilities,
and what do I mean by that?

00:10:26.470 --> 00:10:31.640 align:middle line:84%
I mean that basically
quantum physics is telling us

00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:36.440 align:middle line:84%
that the universe doesn't
come into being as one thing.

00:10:36.440 --> 00:10:40.928 align:middle line:84%
It comes into being as
many possible universes

00:10:40.928 --> 00:10:41.553 align:middle line:90%
simultaneously.

00:10:41.553 --> 00:10:43.100 align:middle line:90%


00:10:43.100 --> 00:10:47.300 align:middle line:84%
And that's the latest dope,
and this latest dope, I mean,

00:10:47.300 --> 00:10:48.790 align:middle line:90%
it sounds dopey.

00:10:48.790 --> 00:10:51.250 align:middle line:84%
How can there be more
than one uni-- universe

00:10:51.250 --> 00:10:52.060 align:middle line:90%
is a singular word.

00:10:52.060 --> 00:10:53.060 align:middle line:90%
How can it be universes?

00:10:53.060 --> 00:10:54.370 align:middle line:90%


00:10:54.370 --> 00:10:56.310 align:middle line:84%
Call them multiverses
if you want to.

00:10:56.310 --> 00:10:57.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or parallel universes.

00:10:57.560 --> 00:10:59.020 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Parallel
universes, a book

00:10:59.020 --> 00:11:00.645 align:middle line:84%
that I wrote about
that subject matter.

00:11:00.645 --> 00:11:03.470 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, so when we look at
all these possibilities,

00:11:03.470 --> 00:11:09.120 align:middle line:84%
we might think about a kid
who's thinking, what am I to do?

00:11:09.120 --> 00:11:11.980 align:middle line:84%
So he's pondering, and
thinking, and worrying.

00:11:11.980 --> 00:11:13.700 align:middle line:90%
And he gets an idea.

00:11:13.700 --> 00:11:16.390 align:middle line:84%
An idea props,
comes into his head

00:11:16.390 --> 00:11:20.710 align:middle line:84%
and then suddenly something
begins to emerge in his mind.

00:11:20.710 --> 00:11:23.770 align:middle line:84%
And when that thing
emerges, something pops.

00:11:23.770 --> 00:11:27.055 align:middle line:84%
And when that thing pops,
we suddenly have, oh--

00:11:27.055 --> 00:11:28.975 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: An idea.

00:11:28.975 --> 00:11:35.960 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: An idea, a star, or
twinkle, twinkle little bat,

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:38.070 align:middle line:90%
how I wonder what you're at.

00:11:38.070 --> 00:11:38.945 align:middle line:90%


00:11:38.945 --> 00:11:40.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Did you write that?

00:11:40.070 --> 00:11:41.231 align:middle line:90%


00:11:41.231 --> 00:11:45.871 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: I'm sure somebody very
clever in the biz wrote that.

00:11:45.871 --> 00:11:46.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:11:46.370 --> 00:11:48.490 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And now we
have an idea appearing.

00:11:48.490 --> 00:11:52.500 align:middle line:84%
So now I try to map out with
our favorite characters-- there

00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:56.327 align:middle line:84%
actually originally four Marx
brothers-- how this might look.

00:11:56.327 --> 00:11:58.160 align:middle line:84%
And how it might look
is that we started out

00:11:58.160 --> 00:12:00.720 align:middle line:84%
with what I call a
precedent blur, which

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.440 align:middle line:90%
means many possibilities.

00:12:02.440 --> 00:12:03.590 align:middle line:90%
We don't know which one.

00:12:03.590 --> 00:12:05.120 align:middle line:84%
And we're all
looking and thinking

00:12:05.120 --> 00:12:07.740 align:middle line:84%
and trying to find out
which one is the right one.

00:12:07.740 --> 00:12:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly we
have a focal point.

00:12:09.930 --> 00:12:12.510 align:middle line:84%
Now the guys concentrate,
oh, we've got an idea.

00:12:12.510 --> 00:12:15.576 align:middle line:84%
A focal point is when something
starts to say, yeah, that's it!

00:12:15.576 --> 00:12:16.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You get
out of confusion.

00:12:16.950 --> 00:12:17.830 align:middle line:90%
You get into a status.

00:12:17.830 --> 00:12:19.038 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Get out of confusion.

00:12:19.038 --> 00:12:24.240 align:middle line:84%
Get out of, let's say, multi
fusion into single fusion,

00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:27.420 align:middle line:84%
and it's rather not a
confusion of different fusions,

00:12:27.420 --> 00:12:32.110 align:middle line:84%
it's really a diffuseness
into an actual fusion event.

00:12:32.110 --> 00:12:34.770 align:middle line:84%
And then we have afterwards
a subsequent blur,

00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:37.290 align:middle line:84%
because you can't
hang on to anything.

00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:40.460 align:middle line:90%
Ideas fly, they flow.

00:12:40.460 --> 00:12:43.250 align:middle line:84%
So this represents
what I would call

00:12:43.250 --> 00:12:46.310 align:middle line:84%
a way of looking at
how the mind works.

00:12:46.310 --> 00:12:48.230 align:middle line:84%
What happens is that,
in the universe,

00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:51.510 align:middle line:84%
we have these bubbles
of possibilities

00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:54.030 align:middle line:84%
all over the place and
focal points appearing

00:12:54.030 --> 00:12:55.080 align:middle line:90%
all over the place.

00:12:55.080 --> 00:12:56.540 align:middle line:90%
It's like a light show.

00:12:56.540 --> 00:12:58.732 align:middle line:84%
We don't see this
because we're in,

00:12:58.732 --> 00:13:00.680 align:middle line:84%
we're made of that
kind of stuff.

00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:03.760 align:middle line:84%
But these are the points, these
are the things that occur,

00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:07.900 align:middle line:84%
and every time they
occur with a focal point,

00:13:07.900 --> 00:13:09.735 align:middle line:90%
something else starts to emerge.

00:13:09.735 --> 00:13:11.390 align:middle line:90%


00:13:11.390 --> 00:13:17.970 align:middle line:84%
We might call it an order, a
sequencing, a reason, a cause

00:13:17.970 --> 00:13:18.610 align:middle line:90%
and effect.

00:13:18.610 --> 00:13:21.660 align:middle line:84%
In fact, cause and
effect are what

00:13:21.660 --> 00:13:23.620 align:middle line:90%
we call in physics causality.

00:13:23.620 --> 00:13:24.720 align:middle line:90%


00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:27.000 align:middle line:84%
It's a very important
part of learning

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:30.660 align:middle line:84%
to gain control of
what's going on.

00:13:30.660 --> 00:13:34.450 align:middle line:84%
We have to learn how to
control what's going-- ever

00:13:34.450 --> 00:13:39.350 align:middle line:84%
since the caves when the Ooga
Boogas were outside and were

00:13:39.350 --> 00:13:41.386 align:middle line:84%
getting clobbered
by those guys, we

00:13:41.386 --> 00:13:43.510 align:middle line:84%
had to learn what are the
tricks to getting control

00:13:43.510 --> 00:13:45.902 align:middle line:84%
over the masses of stuff
that are around us.

00:13:45.902 --> 00:13:47.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So this is what
happens as you grow up,

00:13:47.860 --> 00:13:50.239 align:middle line:84%
you're gaining control
through school of life.

00:13:50.239 --> 00:13:52.280 align:middle line:84%
This is what happens if
you form an organization.

00:13:52.280 --> 00:13:55.600 align:middle line:84%
This is what happens as you get
on with your life, or married,

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:56.100 align:middle line:90%
or whatnot.

00:13:56.100 --> 00:13:59.670 align:middle line:84%
It's just all our attempt
for our mind and the mind--

00:13:59.670 --> 00:14:00.670 align:middle line:90%
universal mind to gain--

00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:01.900 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: --to gain control.

00:14:01.900 --> 00:14:08.360 align:middle line:84%
And control means to observe
or to get hold of something

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:10.850 align:middle line:90%
we call a temporal order.

00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:15.470 align:middle line:84%
An order of the chaotic
bubbles of possibilities.

00:14:15.470 --> 00:14:16.750 align:middle line:90%


00:14:16.750 --> 00:14:20.970 align:middle line:84%
And that starts to emerge
because of the fact

00:14:20.970 --> 00:14:24.690 align:middle line:84%
that there are focal points that
come in every once in awhile.

00:14:24.690 --> 00:14:27.620 align:middle line:84%
And so if we look at
how that all works,

00:14:27.620 --> 00:14:31.220 align:middle line:84%
we have a precedent blur,
a focal point, and then

00:14:31.220 --> 00:14:33.810 align:middle line:84%
we have something
called a posterior blur,

00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:37.200 align:middle line:84%
which isn't as big as
the precedent blur.

00:14:37.200 --> 00:14:42.610 align:middle line:84%
And what that does is it gives
us a temporary or a time order,

00:14:42.610 --> 00:14:44.500 align:middle line:90%
an order of time.

00:14:44.500 --> 00:14:48.900 align:middle line:84%
So we have what I call
a triplet, big blur,

00:14:48.900 --> 00:14:50.700 align:middle line:90%
focal point, small blur.

00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:51.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:54.950 align:middle line:84%
Let me ask you, can this
help us form new ideas?

00:14:54.950 --> 00:14:57.700 align:middle line:84%
Could help us go-- let's talk
about going into the past

00:14:57.700 --> 00:14:59.074 align:middle line:90%
and reforming--

00:14:59.074 --> 00:14:59.990 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's coming.

00:14:59.990 --> 00:15:01.100 align:middle line:90%
That's coming up, actually.

00:15:01.100 --> 00:15:01.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:04.140 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: What this is doing
is not forming a new idea,

00:15:04.140 --> 00:15:09.200 align:middle line:84%
it's forming an idea based
upon your experience.

00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:11.920 align:middle line:84%
It's like when you first
get on to ride a bicycle.

00:15:11.920 --> 00:15:14.890 align:middle line:84%
Your precedent blur is, I'm all
over the place with my bike,

00:15:14.890 --> 00:15:16.360 align:middle line:90%
but then you focal point.

00:15:16.360 --> 00:15:17.480 align:middle line:90%
Hey, that worked.

00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:19.840 align:middle line:84%
And then you have the
precedent blur where you're not

00:15:19.840 --> 00:15:23.100 align:middle line:84%
making as many errors
as you wiggle on--

00:15:23.100 --> 00:15:25.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're
recalling the past memory

00:15:25.600 --> 00:15:28.034 align:middle line:84%
of what it means to ride
the bike, how not to fall.

00:15:28.034 --> 00:15:29.200 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's coming later.

00:15:29.200 --> 00:15:31.050 align:middle line:84%
This is the first time
you got on the bike.

00:15:31.050 --> 00:15:32.800 align:middle line:84%
You have no memory of
riding the bike yet.

00:15:32.800 --> 00:15:33.970 align:middle line:90%
You just go, oh my god.

00:15:33.970 --> 00:15:36.735 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly, you
peddle, focal point.

00:15:36.735 --> 00:15:41.100 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I got the bike and then,
oh, now I can relax a little bit

00:15:41.100 --> 00:15:42.470 align:middle line:90%
and ride the bike.

00:15:42.470 --> 00:15:44.830 align:middle line:84%
And you can see that, oh,
it's OK to fall a little bit

00:15:44.830 --> 00:15:46.413 align:middle line:84%
to the right or a
little bit the left.

00:15:46.413 --> 00:15:49.070 align:middle line:84%
Oh, in fact, I do fall to the
right or left when I stir.

00:15:49.070 --> 00:15:51.460 align:middle line:90%
So now you begin learning bike.

00:15:51.460 --> 00:15:53.340 align:middle line:84%
And learning bike
is just a question

00:15:53.340 --> 00:15:55.440 align:middle line:90%
of playing with these triplets.

00:15:55.440 --> 00:15:56.800 align:middle line:90%


00:15:56.800 --> 00:15:58.420 align:middle line:84%
This is all the
learning experience.

00:15:58.420 --> 00:16:00.020 align:middle line:84%
This is all the
ordering experience.

00:16:00.020 --> 00:16:02.560 align:middle line:84%
This is all going
forward in time.

00:16:02.560 --> 00:16:05.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we go from
children to adolescents

00:16:05.330 --> 00:16:08.300 align:middle line:84%
to adults who constantly is
going from the precedent blur,

00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:11.350 align:middle line:84%
to the focal point,
to the posterior blur.

00:16:11.350 --> 00:16:13.310 align:middle line:84%
That's the quantum physics
explanation of life.

00:16:13.310 --> 00:16:16.170 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: That basically is
what we do when we learn,

00:16:16.170 --> 00:16:20.310 align:middle line:84%
but it's not all of it
because if-- you see,

00:16:20.310 --> 00:16:23.330 align:middle line:84%
after a certain point,
you don't want-- I mean,

00:16:23.330 --> 00:16:25.900 align:middle line:84%
you start to forget stuff,
or at a certain point,

00:16:25.900 --> 00:16:27.100 align:middle line:90%
you want to learn new stuff.

00:16:27.100 --> 00:16:30.000 align:middle line:84%
And the old stuff
might get in the way.

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:32.790 align:middle line:84%
For example, if you're
taught that the only way

00:16:32.790 --> 00:16:40.470 align:middle line:84%
to handle your spouse is to
yell to get what you want,

00:16:40.470 --> 00:16:43.120 align:middle line:84%
then you find that when
you're in the office,

00:16:43.120 --> 00:16:44.670 align:middle line:90%
you yell to get what you want.

00:16:44.670 --> 00:16:46.745 align:middle line:84%
When you go home, you
yell what you could-- You

00:16:46.745 --> 00:16:48.369 align:middle line:84%
yell at your children,
and finally, you

00:16:48.369 --> 00:16:52.100 align:middle line:84%
have this thing that you learned
because your parents maybe

00:16:52.100 --> 00:16:54.150 align:middle line:84%
yelled at you when
you were growing up

00:16:54.150 --> 00:16:56.710 align:middle line:84%
because that way you
behaved and so forth.

00:16:56.710 --> 00:16:58.610 align:middle line:90%
So you become a yeller.

00:16:58.610 --> 00:17:01.480 align:middle line:84%
But that's not the best way
to handle people, is it?

00:17:01.480 --> 00:17:03.930 align:middle line:84%
So you have to learn
how to forget that.

00:17:03.930 --> 00:17:05.680 align:middle line:84%
So there is another
possible-- there's

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:10.359 align:middle line:84%
another way in which order
can-- I call it de-merge

00:17:10.359 --> 00:17:12.910 align:middle line:84%
rather than emerge,
it de-merges.

00:17:12.910 --> 00:17:15.770 align:middle line:84%
You start to lose
touch with that order.

00:17:15.770 --> 00:17:20.060 align:middle line:84%
So a study of a precedent
blur, which is maybe small,

00:17:20.060 --> 00:17:23.420 align:middle line:84%
then a focal point, and
then a posterior blue,

00:17:23.420 --> 00:17:25.760 align:middle line:84%
which is larger, which
means at this point,

00:17:25.760 --> 00:17:28.770 align:middle line:84%
you have fewer
possibilities merging

00:17:28.770 --> 00:17:31.170 align:middle line:90%
into more possibilities.

00:17:31.170 --> 00:17:31.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:17:31.870 --> 00:17:35.250 align:middle line:84%
So that's how we start to fine
tune what it is that we want.

00:17:35.250 --> 00:17:35.750 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: No.

00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:37.949 align:middle line:84%
I would not say fine
tune, it's de-tune.

00:17:37.949 --> 00:17:38.615 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: De-tune.

00:17:38.615 --> 00:17:39.820 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: De-tune.

00:17:39.820 --> 00:17:42.400 align:middle line:84%
Let go of everything
you thought you knew.

00:17:42.400 --> 00:17:43.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love it.

00:17:43.150 --> 00:17:45.025 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: --in order to
do something different.

00:17:45.025 --> 00:17:46.950 align:middle line:84%
If you're an actor,
for example, and you're

00:17:46.950 --> 00:17:49.589 align:middle line:84%
asked to play a female
when you're a male,

00:17:49.589 --> 00:17:51.880 align:middle line:84%
you've got to let go of
whatever you thought a male is.

00:17:51.880 --> 00:17:52.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:54.430 align:middle line:84%
But that happens
everywhere in life

00:17:54.430 --> 00:17:56.210 align:middle line:84%
where you have to let
go of old patterns.

00:17:56.210 --> 00:17:59.480 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: You've got to learn
to let go of the old patterns

00:17:59.480 --> 00:18:00.870 align:middle line:90%
in order to learn the new ones.

00:18:00.870 --> 00:18:04.700 align:middle line:84%
It's the old proverb of the
glass half full and half empty.

00:18:04.700 --> 00:18:08.790 align:middle line:84%
People that don't let
go always have a glass

00:18:08.790 --> 00:18:10.340 align:middle line:90%
which is one way or the other.

00:18:10.340 --> 00:18:12.610 align:middle line:84%
I forgot which way is
considered one way or the other.

00:18:12.610 --> 00:18:13.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We're all half empty.

00:18:13.830 --> 00:18:14.330 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:18:14.330 --> 00:18:15.330 align:middle line:90%


00:18:15.330 --> 00:18:17.850 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Let's say the
half-filled people are

00:18:17.850 --> 00:18:20.680 align:middle line:84%
the ones that hold on
because they can only

00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:22.680 align:middle line:90%
take so much more water in.

00:18:22.680 --> 00:18:24.613 align:middle line:84%
But the half empty people
realize, oh, there's

00:18:24.613 --> 00:18:26.175 align:middle line:90%
a lot more water I can add.

00:18:26.175 --> 00:18:27.521 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It might be the reverse.

00:18:27.521 --> 00:18:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Who knows?

00:18:28.270 --> 00:18:30.000 align:middle line:84%
I get those two
confused all the time.

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:31.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because your
glass is always full.

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:31.961 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:18:31.961 --> 00:18:32.870 align:middle line:90%


00:18:32.870 --> 00:18:35.710 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: The whole point is
empty the glass completely

00:18:35.710 --> 00:18:37.120 align:middle line:90%
in order to let in new stuff.

00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:39.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I love how you
fine tune what I'm saying.

00:18:39.560 --> 00:18:42.810 align:middle line:84%
I love it because you really
do think about these things.

00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:45.170 align:middle line:84%
How did you even get
into quantum physics?

00:18:45.170 --> 00:18:48.260 align:middle line:84%
What sparked your
curiosity around it?

00:18:48.260 --> 00:18:49.175 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Magic.

00:18:49.175 --> 00:18:49.805 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:18:49.805 --> 00:18:51.190 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Magic.

00:18:51.190 --> 00:18:58.900 align:middle line:84%
You see, as a child,
I matured very early.

00:18:58.900 --> 00:19:02.050 align:middle line:84%
At nine years old, I
realized there was sex.

00:19:02.050 --> 00:19:03.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:19:03.110 --> 00:19:04.165 align:middle line:90%
That is early.

00:19:04.165 --> 00:19:05.790 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: That's pretty
early, but I also

00:19:05.790 --> 00:19:08.570 align:middle line:90%
developed a very strange thing.

00:19:08.570 --> 00:19:13.730 align:middle line:84%
I began stammering so badly
that my mother thought

00:19:13.730 --> 00:19:16.350 align:middle line:84%
something had gone
wrong with my brain

00:19:16.350 --> 00:19:18.980 align:middle line:84%
as a result of early
sexual maturation.

00:19:18.980 --> 00:19:21.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you have
older brothers or sisters?

00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:21.240 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: No.

00:19:21.240 --> 00:19:22.005 align:middle line:90%
I was the oldest.

00:19:22.005 --> 00:19:23.260 align:middle line:90%


00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:25.830 align:middle line:84%
So my mom took me
first-- I grew up

00:19:25.830 --> 00:19:29.720 align:middle line:84%
in Chicago-- she took me
to Northwestern University

00:19:29.720 --> 00:19:32.910 align:middle line:84%
to see if they want to
drill in my head to let out

00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:35.670 align:middle line:84%
brain pressure or
something like that.

00:19:35.670 --> 00:19:37.150 align:middle line:90%
And my mom said no to that.

00:19:37.150 --> 00:19:38.770 align:middle line:84%
I finally learned--
I finally got

00:19:38.770 --> 00:19:40.650 align:middle line:84%
ahold of a speech
teacher-- or my mother

00:19:40.650 --> 00:19:45.530 align:middle line:84%
took me to one who taught
me meditation, breathing

00:19:45.530 --> 00:19:50.200 align:middle line:84%
and watching your
breath, in and out.

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:51.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: At what age?

00:19:51.340 --> 00:19:52.122 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: 10.

00:19:52.122 --> 00:19:52.955 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:19:52.955 --> 00:19:53.400 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: 11.

00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:53.899 align:middle line:90%
12.

00:19:53.899 --> 00:19:54.860 align:middle line:90%


00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:58.350 align:middle line:84%
So I began to learn
this sort of stuff,

00:19:58.350 --> 00:20:02.740 align:middle line:84%
and then what I would do to
improve my speaking skill

00:20:02.740 --> 00:20:06.620 align:middle line:84%
is I would practice doing
magic in front of a mirror.

00:20:06.620 --> 00:20:07.967 align:middle line:90%


00:20:07.967 --> 00:20:09.550 align:middle line:84%
I would stand in
front of the mirror--

00:20:09.550 --> 00:20:09.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How would that
help your speaking?

00:20:09.970 --> 00:20:13.500 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Because when you do a
magic trick, you gotta talk.

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:15.420 align:middle line:90%


00:20:15.420 --> 00:20:17.350 align:middle line:90%
In magic, they call it patter.

00:20:17.350 --> 00:20:20.880 align:middle line:84%
And often magicians think
of patter as being useless,

00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:21.380 align:middle line:90%
unh-uh.

00:20:21.380 --> 00:20:22.410 align:middle line:90%


00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:26.550 align:middle line:84%
Being a magician is like
being a one-act play.

00:20:26.550 --> 00:20:27.820 align:middle line:90%
You are the whole thing.

00:20:27.820 --> 00:20:32.060 align:middle line:84%
You're not only the
presenter of the data

00:20:32.060 --> 00:20:35.190 align:middle line:84%
or the thing which is the
story which is being told,

00:20:35.190 --> 00:20:36.650 align:middle line:90%
you're acting it out.

00:20:36.650 --> 00:20:37.600 align:middle line:90%
You're the stage.

00:20:37.600 --> 00:20:39.810 align:middle line:84%
You're the props
because your props are

00:20:39.810 --> 00:20:43.450 align:middle line:84%
the cards or the things or
whatever you're manipulating,

00:20:43.450 --> 00:20:44.850 align:middle line:90%
but if you ain't talking,

00:20:44.850 --> 00:20:46.150 align:middle line:90%
I mean, some magicians do that.

00:20:46.150 --> 00:20:48.880 align:middle line:84%
They just do all visual,
and they're fine.

00:20:48.880 --> 00:20:51.210 align:middle line:84%
But that's like
watching a mime perform.

00:20:51.210 --> 00:20:52.330 align:middle line:90%
That's fine.

00:20:52.330 --> 00:20:54.645 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You have to be really
good in order to do that.

00:20:54.645 --> 00:20:56.310 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well you
just got to remember

00:20:56.310 --> 00:20:59.070 align:middle line:84%
that you've got everybody's
focus on just what you're

00:20:59.070 --> 00:21:02.950 align:middle line:84%
doing visually, but if
you're a performer who

00:21:02.950 --> 00:21:08.530 align:middle line:84%
does what I call magic,
you've got to use your voice.

00:21:08.530 --> 00:21:09.570 align:middle line:90%
The voice is everything.

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:14.400 align:middle line:84%
In fact, if you have a good
way of presenting your trick,

00:21:14.400 --> 00:21:16.447 align:middle line:84%
people remember different
things about the trick

00:21:16.447 --> 00:21:19.030 align:middle line:84%
that have nothing to do with the
way you really did the trick.

00:21:19.030 --> 00:21:21.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you obviously
got over your stammering.

00:21:21.560 --> 00:21:25.240 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Took me a while,
and I still am a stammerer,

00:21:25.240 --> 00:21:28.760 align:middle line:84%
but I-- in fact, you
can find me stammering

00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:31.660 align:middle line:84%
under certain
occasions that arise,

00:21:31.660 --> 00:21:33.190 align:middle line:90%
but I found out ways to do it.

00:21:33.190 --> 00:21:36.010 align:middle line:84%
So actually, in a
way, I definitely

00:21:36.010 --> 00:21:38.135 align:middle line:84%
have improved my
speaking ability

00:21:38.135 --> 00:21:39.510 align:middle line:84%
because now I'm
a public speaker.

00:21:39.510 --> 00:21:41.843 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're a presenter,
and you're a phenomenal one.

00:21:41.843 --> 00:21:41.967 align:middle line:90%


00:21:41.967 --> 00:21:43.300 align:middle line:90%
And you have-- look what you do.

00:21:43.300 --> 00:21:45.662 align:middle line:84%
You take the complex
and you make it simple,

00:21:45.662 --> 00:21:47.620 align:middle line:84%
and that's basically what
you did in your life.

00:21:47.620 --> 00:21:48.460 align:middle line:90%
I never knew that.

00:21:48.460 --> 00:21:49.700 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:21:49.700 --> 00:21:51.530 align:middle line:84%
But the beautiful
thing about it is

00:21:51.530 --> 00:21:55.420 align:middle line:84%
that you healed something and
then became a teacher of it.

00:21:55.420 --> 00:21:55.920 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:58.560 align:middle line:84%
And it's very important
to realize that,

00:21:58.560 --> 00:22:01.230 align:middle line:84%
that I did a little
kind of history

00:22:01.230 --> 00:22:04.210 align:middle line:84%
of all of the
so-called greats that

00:22:04.210 --> 00:22:06.890 align:middle line:90%
have ever appeared in life.

00:22:06.890 --> 00:22:08.890 align:middle line:90%
By greats, I mean great actors--

00:22:08.890 --> 00:22:10.410 align:middle line:90%


00:22:10.410 --> 00:22:11.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Leaders.

00:22:11.120 --> 00:22:14.120 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: --presidents,
leaders, basketball players.

00:22:14.120 --> 00:22:17.000 align:middle line:84%
I just recently found
out that Shaq O'Neal

00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:19.144 align:middle line:90%
was a stutterer and stammerer.

00:22:19.144 --> 00:22:20.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So all of
these people had

00:22:20.560 --> 00:22:21.851 align:middle line:90%
to come over massive adversity.

00:22:21.851 --> 00:22:25.470 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: They all had
to overcome hurdles.

00:22:25.470 --> 00:22:27.990 align:middle line:84%
So if you out there
in the audience

00:22:27.990 --> 00:22:32.530 align:middle line:84%
are feeling that you can never
be a success because you have

00:22:32.530 --> 00:22:35.970 align:middle line:84%
this particular
impediment, consider

00:22:35.970 --> 00:22:41.380 align:middle line:84%
yourself blessed far more
than the guy next door who's

00:22:41.380 --> 00:22:43.140 align:middle line:90%
got no impediments at all.

00:22:43.140 --> 00:22:44.845 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: He should go find one.

00:22:44.845 --> 00:22:45.420 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Yes.

00:22:45.420 --> 00:22:48.160 align:middle line:84%
If you want to
succeed at doing even

00:22:48.160 --> 00:22:50.750 align:middle line:84%
what you think is
something you can't

00:22:50.750 --> 00:22:54.120 align:middle line:84%
do because of the impediment,
I want to tell you you can.

00:22:54.120 --> 00:22:55.870 align:middle line:84%
I don't care what
your impediment is,

00:22:55.870 --> 00:22:58.360 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be
able to overcome it.

00:22:58.360 --> 00:22:59.940 align:middle line:90%
I'm speaking from experience.

00:22:59.940 --> 00:23:01.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm a speaker.

00:23:01.310 --> 00:23:04.050 align:middle line:84%
I overcome stammering,
psychological problems.

00:23:04.050 --> 00:23:05.240 align:middle line:90%
You can overcome it.

00:23:05.240 --> 00:23:08.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How did you tie in
quantum physics to that?

00:23:08.630 --> 00:23:11.260 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, that's where
the story gets started.

00:23:11.260 --> 00:23:13.310 align:middle line:84%
It gets started with
magic because magic

00:23:13.310 --> 00:23:14.730 align:middle line:90%
is in front of a mirror.

00:23:14.730 --> 00:23:19.940 align:middle line:84%
And so I began to wonder about--
I mean, I began to wonder,

00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:21.340 align:middle line:90%
and that's the next thing.

00:23:21.340 --> 00:23:23.900 align:middle line:90%
I began to wonder about.

00:23:23.900 --> 00:23:28.160 align:middle line:84%
And once I started to
wonder about how things are,

00:23:28.160 --> 00:23:31.740 align:middle line:84%
I began to wonder, what is
this thing called light?

00:23:31.740 --> 00:23:35.560 align:middle line:84%
And just thinking about
light got me into physics.

00:23:35.560 --> 00:23:38.650 align:middle line:84%
So I looked at all
the college curricula

00:23:38.650 --> 00:23:41.220 align:middle line:84%
I could take when I
went to university,

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:45.260 align:middle line:84%
and nothing interested
me as much as physics,

00:23:45.260 --> 00:23:47.680 align:middle line:84%
because in physics
I was learning

00:23:47.680 --> 00:23:50.450 align:middle line:84%
the magic of how
the universe works.

00:23:50.450 --> 00:23:53.610 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I was learning
how the tricks are performed.

00:23:53.610 --> 00:23:56.030 align:middle line:84%
I kind of think of God as a
great performing magician.

00:23:56.030 --> 00:23:57.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great.

00:23:57.060 --> 00:24:00.820 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And so-- and then
all of us are the audience,

00:24:00.820 --> 00:24:04.620 align:middle line:84%
but we're also the
performer-- we're also

00:24:04.620 --> 00:24:06.570 align:middle line:84%
the magicians,
performers themselves.

00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:09.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're the observer and
the performer at the same time.

00:24:09.970 --> 00:24:10.080 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: And the observed.

00:24:10.080 --> 00:24:10.710 align:middle line:90%
The same time.

00:24:10.710 --> 00:24:12.126 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The observer
and observed.

00:24:12.126 --> 00:24:16.657 align:middle line:84%
So light gets us into
the concept of-- now

00:24:16.657 --> 00:24:18.490 align:middle line:84%
this is where we get
into the physics of it.

00:24:18.490 --> 00:24:20.750 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Yes, and we're
going to come up on that.

00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:24.140 align:middle line:84%
So let-- just let
me briefly-- should

00:24:24.140 --> 00:24:26.610 align:middle line:84%
I go briefly through
the rest of this?

00:24:26.610 --> 00:24:27.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh,no, take your time.

00:24:27.860 --> 00:24:28.930 align:middle line:90%
We love the details.

00:24:28.930 --> 00:24:29.690 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:24:29.690 --> 00:24:30.190 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:24:30.190 --> 00:24:33.040 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So we're back to
looking at this whole thing

00:24:33.040 --> 00:24:38.710 align:middle line:84%
about letting go, and what that
means is your precedent blur is

00:24:38.710 --> 00:24:41.340 align:middle line:84%
smaller than your
posterior blur,

00:24:41.340 --> 00:24:44.450 align:middle line:84%
in other words, what came
before is pretty well defined,

00:24:44.450 --> 00:24:47.220 align:middle line:84%
but what came after
is less well defined.

00:24:47.220 --> 00:24:48.780 align:middle line:90%
You're letting go.

00:24:48.780 --> 00:24:51.020 align:middle line:90%
You're letting go.

00:24:51.020 --> 00:24:54.850 align:middle line:84%
And letting go is
a remarkable thing

00:24:54.850 --> 00:24:59.740 align:middle line:84%
that everybody should learn
because you can't focus

00:24:59.740 --> 00:25:01.970 align:middle line:90%
unless you let go to begin with.

00:25:01.970 --> 00:25:04.260 align:middle line:84%
So this is a very
important part.

00:25:04.260 --> 00:25:06.620 align:middle line:84%
Letting go and focusing,
there is a dance

00:25:06.620 --> 00:25:10.000 align:middle line:84%
that you have to go through,
and you have the intent and will

00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:11.500 align:middle line:90%
to make it happen.

00:25:11.500 --> 00:25:14.440 align:middle line:84%
So here's a kind of a picture
of what this might look like,

00:25:14.440 --> 00:25:16.790 align:middle line:84%
a sequence of events
in which somebody

00:25:16.790 --> 00:25:19.950 align:middle line:84%
is learning to do something,
and as the sequence goes

00:25:19.950 --> 00:25:23.800 align:middle line:84%
on from a beginning
blur of possibilities

00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:26.790 align:middle line:84%
and to focal points and then
less and less possibilities,

00:25:26.790 --> 00:25:29.910 align:middle line:84%
we're really learning
and we're striving

00:25:29.910 --> 00:25:32.400 align:middle line:84%
to become an expert
at something.

00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:33.870 align:middle line:90%
This is called mastery.

00:25:33.870 --> 00:25:39.350 align:middle line:84%
This is what mastery looks
like as far as your-- learning

00:25:39.350 --> 00:25:40.860 align:middle line:90%
your mind, how your mind works.

00:25:40.860 --> 00:25:41.360 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:25:41.360 --> 00:25:42.026 align:middle line:90%
Quantum physics.

00:25:42.026 --> 00:25:44.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is mind
mastery, so it's basically

00:25:44.480 --> 00:25:48.170 align:middle line:84%
how we understand our
developmental stages.

00:25:48.170 --> 00:25:50.720 align:middle line:84%
You can take this
from a macro view,

00:25:50.720 --> 00:25:52.920 align:middle line:84%
and you can look at the
evolutionary biology,

00:25:52.920 --> 00:25:55.040 align:middle line:84%
or you can take it
from a micro view

00:25:55.040 --> 00:25:58.180 align:middle line:84%
and look at your own personality
and your own evolution.

00:25:58.180 --> 00:25:58.865 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Exactly.

00:25:58.865 --> 00:26:02.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is how it goes
from a blur, to the focus,

00:26:02.730 --> 00:26:05.890 align:middle line:84%
to something that's less
controlled but solid.

00:26:05.890 --> 00:26:08.380 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Actually,
just the opposite.

00:26:08.380 --> 00:26:10.090 align:middle line:84%
We're going into more
and more control.

00:26:10.090 --> 00:26:13.160 align:middle line:84%
This is what I would say
is the story of evolution.

00:26:13.160 --> 00:26:16.710 align:middle line:84%
This is the actual- we're
going to get to the other way.

00:26:16.710 --> 00:26:18.530 align:middle line:90%
That's going the other way.

00:26:18.530 --> 00:26:22.380 align:middle line:84%
Getting from more possibility
to less possibility

00:26:22.380 --> 00:26:24.970 align:middle line:90%
is becoming an expert.

00:26:24.970 --> 00:26:27.100 align:middle line:90%
So we're going that way in time.

00:26:27.100 --> 00:26:29.980 align:middle line:84%
That's what you do when you
learn to do something well.

00:26:29.980 --> 00:26:32.175 align:middle line:84%
So that's what this
picture is showing us.

00:26:32.175 --> 00:26:35.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, how does this
relate to time travel?

00:26:35.950 --> 00:26:38.590 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, that's
coming up too.

00:26:38.590 --> 00:26:43.260 align:middle line:84%
So it's just a matter of how
fast you want to go here.

00:26:43.260 --> 00:26:45.940 align:middle line:84%
These are-- I'm just
showing triplets

00:26:45.940 --> 00:26:49.300 align:middle line:84%
that recognize the different
aspects of-- but we

00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:50.630 align:middle line:90%
don't need to go through that.

00:26:50.630 --> 00:26:52.450 align:middle line:90%
ok, now, here's something else.

00:26:52.450 --> 00:26:54.960 align:middle line:84%
Here we're doing what you
just were talking about,

00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:56.650 align:middle line:90%
it's the letting go process.

00:26:56.650 --> 00:27:00.030 align:middle line:84%
We're starting out from
something we know is true.

00:27:00.030 --> 00:27:04.530 align:middle line:84%
By golly, this is the absolute
truth, to I don't know.

00:27:04.530 --> 00:27:05.990 align:middle line:90%
I'm not so sure it's true.

00:27:05.990 --> 00:27:08.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So when we say, oh, I
used to believe such and such,

00:27:08.600 --> 00:27:10.970 align:middle line:90%
and I used to think this way.

00:27:10.970 --> 00:27:12.074 align:middle line:90%
