And those funny-looking letters
that you see on the screen

00:59:34.050 --> 00:59:35.880 align:middle line:84%
right there are really
the same letters

00:59:35.880 --> 00:59:37.880 align:middle line:84%
that I just mentioned but
written out in Hebrew.

00:59:37.880 --> 00:59:38.980 align:middle line:90%


00:59:38.980 --> 00:59:41.930 align:middle line:84%
The thing is, when you get into
a study of the sacred meaning

00:59:41.930 --> 00:59:47.720 align:middle line:84%
of things, we have something
we call Kabbalah, or Kabbalah,

00:59:47.720 --> 00:59:49.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In different ways.

00:59:49.510 --> 00:59:52.160 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: And it means to receive.

00:59:52.160 --> 00:59:55.040 align:middle line:84%
So the Kabbalah is
something you receive.

00:59:55.040 --> 00:59:58.940 align:middle line:84%
If you go to a restaurant
in Tel Aviv, for example,

00:59:58.940 --> 01:00:01.740 align:middle line:84%
and you have a meal
and you want a receipt,

01:00:01.740 --> 01:00:04.840 align:middle line:84%
you say to the waiter
Kabala Bevakasha, which

01:00:04.840 --> 01:00:07.090 align:middle line:84%
means I want-- give me
the receipt, please.

01:00:07.090 --> 01:00:08.760 align:middle line:90%


01:00:08.760 --> 01:00:09.954 align:middle line:90%
It can be used another way.

01:00:09.954 --> 01:00:12.120 align:middle line:84%
Kabbalah can mean a receipt,
or it means to receive.

01:00:12.120 --> 01:00:13.286 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or a major religion.

01:00:13.286 --> 01:00:14.680 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Or a major religion.

01:00:14.680 --> 01:00:17.440 align:middle line:84%
So it's a study of the
meaning of the Hebrew letters

01:00:17.440 --> 01:00:20.480 align:middle line:84%
themselves, and each
letter has a meaning.

01:00:20.480 --> 01:00:23.740 align:middle line:84%
So when you look at this phrase,
"God said, let there be light

01:00:23.740 --> 01:00:27.700 align:middle line:84%
and there was light," it
has a very special meaning.

01:00:27.700 --> 01:00:28.200 align:middle line:90%
Vayomer

01:00:28.200 --> 01:00:30.010 align:middle line:90%
Elohim Yehi-or Vayehi-or.

01:00:30.010 --> 01:00:31.680 align:middle line:90%


01:00:31.680 --> 01:00:33.400 align:middle line:90%
And this is what it means.

01:00:33.400 --> 01:00:34.970 align:middle line:90%


01:00:34.970 --> 01:00:40.600 align:middle line:84%
Vayomer is the
saying, and God said,

01:00:40.600 --> 01:00:46.070 align:middle line:84%
is saying spirit is
coming into existence.

01:00:46.070 --> 01:00:48.525 align:middle line:84%
Spirit is entering
into existence.

01:00:48.525 --> 01:00:49.650 align:middle line:90%


01:00:49.650 --> 01:00:53.380 align:middle line:90%
That's what Vayomer means.

01:00:53.380 --> 01:00:58.450 align:middle line:84%
Then we have Elohim, and Elohim
is the Hebrew word for God.

01:00:58.450 --> 01:01:01.030 align:middle line:84%
It's actually the
plural of gods,

01:01:01.030 --> 01:01:03.940 align:middle line:84%
which is not often mentioned
in the sacred writings,

01:01:03.940 --> 01:01:05.240 align:middle line:90%
but it really means gods.

01:01:05.240 --> 01:01:06.420 align:middle line:90%


01:01:06.420 --> 01:01:10.880 align:middle line:84%
It means spirit is moving
life and moving life

01:01:10.880 --> 01:01:13.280 align:middle line:84%
at the same time it's
doing something else,

01:01:13.280 --> 01:01:15.410 align:middle line:90%
and this is very important.

01:01:15.410 --> 01:01:18.560 align:middle line:84%
Elohim means not
only moving life,

01:01:18.560 --> 01:01:23.611 align:middle line:84%
but it also means bringing in
a resistance to that movement.

01:01:23.611 --> 01:01:24.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What does that create?

01:01:24.860 --> 01:01:25.494 align:middle line:90%
A resistance.

01:01:25.494 --> 01:01:26.035 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Mind.

01:01:26.035 --> 01:01:27.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mind.

01:01:27.550 --> 01:01:30.317 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: A mind which
resists the movement.

01:01:30.317 --> 01:01:30.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

01:01:30.900 --> 01:01:32.233 align:middle line:90%
So that's where the observer is.

01:01:32.233 --> 01:01:34.980 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: That's where the
observer is coming into.

01:01:34.980 --> 01:01:37.920 align:middle line:84%
Then we have Yehi, which
means let there be.

01:01:37.920 --> 01:01:39.020 align:middle line:90%


01:01:39.020 --> 01:01:45.550 align:middle line:84%
Yehi means that life
comes into existence,

01:01:45.550 --> 01:01:48.220 align:middle line:90%
and that gives more existence.

01:01:48.220 --> 01:01:49.646 align:middle line:90%


01:01:49.646 --> 01:01:53.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we have this spirit,
the existence of spirit,

01:01:53.850 --> 01:01:57.630 align:middle line:84%
and then it gets into light, and
then it needs mind, which is--

01:01:57.630 --> 01:02:03.280 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Elohim is the resistance
of the spirit giving rise

01:02:03.280 --> 01:02:06.780 align:middle line:84%
to the movement of
existence, and then we

01:02:06.780 --> 01:02:11.640 align:middle line:84%
have Yehi, which is existence
giving rise to something which

01:02:11.640 --> 01:02:14.500 align:middle line:84%
is a life, giving rise
to existence again.

01:02:14.500 --> 01:02:17.790 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of an
intertwining chain.

01:02:17.790 --> 01:02:20.711 align:middle line:84%
And then we have the next word,
and this is the magical word,

01:02:20.711 --> 01:02:21.210 align:middle line:90%
Or.

01:02:21.210 --> 01:02:22.270 align:middle line:90%


01:02:22.270 --> 01:02:26.060 align:middle line:84%
Aleph-Vav-Reish-- Or is
the Hebrew word for light.

01:02:26.060 --> 01:02:28.090 align:middle line:90%
And Aleph means the spirit.

01:02:28.090 --> 01:02:32.060 align:middle line:84%
Vav means the fertilizing agent,
or that which distributes,

01:02:32.060 --> 01:02:36.190 align:middle line:84%
and Reish, the third letter
is the whole universe.

01:02:36.190 --> 01:02:40.280 align:middle line:84%
So Aleph-Vav-Reish means spirit
fertilizing the whole universe.

01:02:40.280 --> 01:02:43.890 align:middle line:84%
So light means spirit
fertilizing the whole universe.

01:02:43.890 --> 01:02:44.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

01:02:44.790 --> 01:02:46.430 align:middle line:84%
And light is at the
center of everything.

01:02:46.430 --> 01:02:47.005 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Everything.

01:02:47.005 --> 01:02:47.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Everything, yes.

01:02:47.830 --> 01:02:48.621 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: Everything.

01:02:48.621 --> 01:02:50.140 align:middle line:84%
In fact, in many
sacred writings you

01:02:50.140 --> 01:02:53.090 align:middle line:84%
find that God is light, that
it's often said that way.

01:02:53.090 --> 01:02:53.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:02:53.590 --> 01:02:54.350 align:middle line:90%
I am the light.

01:02:54.350 --> 01:02:54.850 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:02:54.850 --> 01:02:56.640 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: So now we
have Yehi-or, then

01:02:56.640 --> 01:03:00.975 align:middle line:84%
we have another
Vayehi, and again.

01:03:00.975 --> 01:03:02.540 align:middle line:90%


01:03:02.540 --> 01:03:03.180 align:middle line:90%
Yayehi-or.

01:03:03.180 --> 01:03:08.390 align:middle line:84%
Two word-- the word Or
is pronounced twice,

01:03:08.390 --> 01:03:10.600 align:middle line:84%
let there be light,
and let there be light.

01:03:10.600 --> 01:03:11.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There is light.

01:03:11.640 --> 01:03:12.140 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:03:12.140 --> 01:03:14.820 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Let there be light
and let there be light,

01:03:14.820 --> 01:03:17.610 align:middle line:90%
two Ors, Aleph-Vav-Reish twice.

01:03:17.610 --> 01:03:18.240 align:middle line:90%
Why twice?

01:03:18.240 --> 01:03:18.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why twice?

01:03:18.720 --> 01:03:20.303 align:middle line:84%
Why two different
references to light?

01:03:20.303 --> 01:03:23.296 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And it turns out this is
very necessary for the universe

01:03:23.296 --> 01:03:23.795 align:middle line:90%
to begin.

01:03:23.795 --> 01:03:24.960 align:middle line:90%


01:03:24.960 --> 01:03:27.280 align:middle line:90%
There are two kinds of light.

01:03:27.280 --> 01:03:30.210 align:middle line:84%
We have light that
zigzags in space,

01:03:30.210 --> 01:03:33.370 align:middle line:84%
which produces what we
call the particles, matter,

01:03:33.370 --> 01:03:35.340 align:middle line:90%
that we existence in.

01:03:35.340 --> 01:03:39.850 align:middle line:84%
And this zigzagging
light that appears,

01:03:39.850 --> 01:03:42.650 align:middle line:84%
when it appears as
matter, turns out

01:03:42.650 --> 01:03:46.570 align:middle line:84%
to make up all of the material
particles of the universe,

01:03:46.570 --> 01:03:51.230 align:middle line:84%
which is basically what we call
the electrons and positrons.

01:03:51.230 --> 01:03:54.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So light slowed
down is this table.

01:03:54.030 --> 01:03:55.020 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: That's right.

01:03:55.020 --> 01:03:55.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:03:55.800 --> 01:03:57.860 align:middle line:90%
So matter is light slowed down.

01:03:57.860 --> 01:04:01.080 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: It slows down
by doing a zigzag dance.

01:04:01.080 --> 01:04:05.160 align:middle line:84%
If I-- Let's say I'm
trying to go that way.

01:04:05.160 --> 01:04:07.230 align:middle line:84%
If I just go that
way, no problem.

01:04:07.230 --> 01:04:09.560 align:middle line:84%
But suppose I want to go
that way by zigzagging?

01:04:09.560 --> 01:04:11.680 align:middle line:84%
