01:12:30.552 --> 01:12:32.635 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Spinning, actually,
in the same direction.

01:12:32.635 --> 01:12:33.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Same direction.

01:12:33.070 --> 01:12:33.570 align:middle line:90%
I see.

01:12:33.570 --> 01:12:37.100 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: But because they're
different orientations--

01:12:37.100 --> 01:12:38.870 align:middle line:84%
see they're both
spinning this way.

01:12:38.870 --> 01:12:41.499 align:middle line:84%
The spin is in the direction
in which your fingers curl,

01:12:41.499 --> 01:12:43.290 align:middle line:84%
but your thumb is
pointing in the direction

01:12:43.290 --> 01:12:44.623 align:middle line:90%
in which the stripes are moving.

01:12:44.623 --> 01:12:47.530 align:middle line:84%
And the stripes are going
in opposite directions.

01:12:47.530 --> 01:12:50.870 align:middle line:84%
This parity reversal
is extremely important.

01:12:50.870 --> 01:12:53.700 align:middle line:84%
This space reversal is
extremely important.

01:12:53.700 --> 01:12:56.630 align:middle line:84%
Without this, there
can be no matter.

01:12:56.630 --> 01:12:57.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

01:12:57.270 --> 01:12:58.250 align:middle line:90%
Now why?

01:12:58.250 --> 01:12:59.810 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: We're going to see.

01:12:59.810 --> 01:13:02.330 align:middle line:84%
Here's something we
call a time symmetry.

01:13:02.330 --> 01:13:05.620 align:middle line:84%
Here we have a
left-handed particle,

01:13:05.620 --> 01:13:10.600 align:middle line:84%
which is curling like this
and the thumb going down.

01:13:10.600 --> 01:13:15.130 align:middle line:84%
If we reflect it in time, which
means we send time backwards,

01:13:15.130 --> 01:13:17.890 align:middle line:84%
it also turns into a
left-handed particle,

01:13:17.890 --> 01:13:20.540 align:middle line:90%
but things get reversed.

01:13:20.540 --> 01:13:23.290 align:middle line:84%
Notice that the stripes
are pointing the same way,

01:13:23.290 --> 01:13:26.100 align:middle line:90%
but the spins are reversed.

01:13:26.100 --> 01:13:27.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All right.

01:13:27.010 --> 01:13:33.644 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: But the-- it's
still left handed.

01:13:33.644 --> 01:13:36.310 align:middle line:84%
On the right side of the picture
is the left hand pointing down,

01:13:36.310 --> 01:13:38.510 align:middle line:84%
left hand pointing up,
and time reversal--

01:13:38.510 --> 01:13:39.600 align:middle line:90%
this is what happens.

01:13:39.600 --> 01:13:40.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Time reversal is what?

01:13:40.850 --> 01:13:41.470 align:middle line:90%
Explain that.

01:13:41.470 --> 01:13:43.200 align:middle line:90%


01:13:43.200 --> 01:13:44.950 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: That's
difficult to explain.

01:13:44.950 --> 01:13:46.642 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This isn't?

01:13:46.642 --> 01:13:47.790 align:middle line:90%
>>WOLF: This isn't.

01:13:47.790 --> 01:13:50.850 align:middle line:84%
Time reversal is
almost like watching

01:13:50.850 --> 01:13:53.080 align:middle line:90%
a movie going backwards in time.

01:13:53.080 --> 01:13:55.800 align:middle line:84%
It turns out that
particles do that, too,

01:13:55.800 --> 01:13:58.097 align:middle line:84%
and that's part of the
way the game is played.

01:13:58.097 --> 01:13:59.513 align:middle line:84%
We'll come to that
a little later.

01:13:59.513 --> 01:14:00.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I don't want to
get any more confused.

01:14:00.570 --> 01:14:00.935 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:14:00.935 --> 01:14:02.440 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And here's
another one which

01:14:02.440 --> 01:14:06.160 align:middle line:84%
we call-- here's time symmetry
with a right-handed particle.

01:14:06.160 --> 01:14:07.210 align:middle line:90%
I just put that in.

01:14:07.210 --> 01:14:08.710 align:middle line:84%
I'll just go through
that very fast.

01:14:08.710 --> 01:14:09.670 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

01:14:09.670 --> 01:14:14.200 align:middle line:84%
And now here's something we call
C symmetry or charge reversal.

01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:17.290 align:middle line:84%
It has the same thing to do
with matter and anti-matter

01:14:17.290 --> 01:14:18.910 align:middle line:90%
coming into existence.

01:14:18.910 --> 01:14:20.510 align:middle line:84%
Here we have a
right-handed particle,

01:14:20.510 --> 01:14:23.080 align:middle line:84%
and when we look to see
on the left-handed side,

01:14:23.080 --> 01:14:25.350 align:middle line:84%
it becomes a
left-handed particle.

01:14:25.350 --> 01:14:30.000 align:middle line:84%
And in this case, the
directions of the barber poles

01:14:30.000 --> 01:14:33.170 align:middle line:84%
are the same, but the
spins are reversed

01:14:33.170 --> 01:14:34.910 align:middle line:90%
and the hands are reversed.

01:14:34.910 --> 01:14:38.030 align:middle line:84%
So when we have
matter to antimatter,

01:14:38.030 --> 01:14:40.640 align:middle line:84%
things get twisted
around, and we'll

01:14:40.640 --> 01:14:42.530 align:middle line:84%
come to that a little
later on, but first

01:14:42.530 --> 01:14:47.350 align:middle line:84%
let me just move now into a
picture of why this parity

01:14:47.350 --> 01:14:49.120 align:middle line:90%
reversal is very important.

01:14:49.120 --> 01:14:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Here is a particle of
matter coming into existence

01:14:54.540 --> 01:14:58.165 align:middle line:84%
and moving at the speed of
light and then going out

01:14:58.165 --> 01:14:58.706 align:middle line:90%
of existence.

01:14:58.706 --> 01:14:59.830 align:middle line:90%


01:14:59.830 --> 01:15:03.130 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly something
called the mind of God

01:15:03.130 --> 01:15:10.210 align:middle line:84%
acts and produces a
right-handed particle, which

01:15:10.210 --> 01:15:13.660 align:middle line:84%
now goes in the
opposite direction,

01:15:13.660 --> 01:15:18.890 align:middle line:84%
goes out of existence, produces
another left-handed particle,

01:15:18.890 --> 01:15:21.720 align:middle line:90%
and we have this famous zigzag.

01:15:21.720 --> 01:15:22.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:15:22.340 --> 01:15:24.260 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: And now
the zigzag is what

01:15:24.260 --> 01:15:26.850 align:middle line:84%
we call an actual
particle of matter.

01:15:26.850 --> 01:15:27.860 align:middle line:90%


01:15:27.860 --> 01:15:29.820 align:middle line:84%
This is what it's made
out of, zigzagging

01:15:29.820 --> 01:15:31.042 align:middle line:90%
particles going very fast.

01:15:31.042 --> 01:15:32.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: These
chairs, these tables.

01:15:32.500 --> 01:15:34.490 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: All the
electrons and the quarks,

01:15:34.490 --> 01:15:36.860 align:middle line:84%
they're all doing this
dance, and they're

01:15:36.860 --> 01:15:40.420 align:middle line:84%
interacting with this field
called the Higgs field or Mind

01:15:40.420 --> 01:15:43.320 align:middle line:84%
of God field, or whatever
you want to call it,

01:15:43.320 --> 01:15:46.265 align:middle line:84%
that's interacting and causing
the zigzag to take place.

01:15:46.265 --> 01:15:48.470 align:middle line:90%


01:15:48.470 --> 01:15:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Now, we're going to
look at a thought.

01:15:50.720 --> 01:15:51.970 align:middle line:90%
Here we have something going--

01:15:51.970 --> 01:15:52.025 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yay.

01:15:52.025 --> 01:15:52.910 align:middle line:90%
We're looking at thoughts now.

01:15:52.910 --> 01:15:54.284 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: We're
looking at thought.

01:15:54.284 --> 01:15:57.630 align:middle line:84%
Here we're looking at something
going backward in time,

01:15:57.630 --> 01:16:00.540 align:middle line:84%
then turning around,
going forward in time,

01:16:00.540 --> 01:16:04.250 align:middle line:84%
then turning around and
going backward in time.

01:16:04.250 --> 01:16:06.740 align:middle line:84%
And what we have here
is when something

01:16:06.740 --> 01:16:09.430 align:middle line:84%
can go backwards and
forwards in time,

01:16:09.430 --> 01:16:12.720 align:middle line:84%
it could literally stay in
space and not go anywhere,

01:16:12.720 --> 01:16:15.210 align:middle line:84%
but time has gotten
frozen for it

01:16:15.210 --> 01:16:17.860 align:middle line:84%
because it's going
nowhere in time.

01:16:17.860 --> 01:16:21.040 align:middle line:84%
In a certain sense, it's
moving through space but not

01:16:21.040 --> 01:16:22.160 align:middle line:90%
through time.

01:16:22.160 --> 01:16:24.400 align:middle line:84%
It's moving faster than
the speed of light.

01:16:24.400 --> 01:16:29.300 align:middle line:84%
We would call that tachyonic or
the action of the mind of God.

01:16:29.300 --> 01:16:33.210 align:middle line:84%
So what we're looking at,
is it all an illusion?

01:16:33.210 --> 01:16:34.725 align:middle line:90%
How does it all work?

01:16:34.725 --> 01:16:35.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:16:35.620 --> 01:16:38.790 align:middle line:84%
And so that's what a
memory-- actually when you

01:16:38.790 --> 01:16:41.070 align:middle line:84%
said they get frozen
in time, that's

01:16:41.070 --> 01:16:43.550 align:middle line:84%
what a past memory frozen
in time would look like?

01:16:43.550 --> 01:16:47.950 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: It's frozen in
time in a certain sense,

01:16:47.950 --> 01:16:51.970 align:middle line:84%
but you see it's moving
through space but not in time,

01:16:51.970 --> 01:16:55.355 align:middle line:84%
and that's, in a way,
how memory works.

01:16:55.355 --> 01:16:57.630 align:middle line:90%


01:16:57.630 --> 01:17:00.330 align:middle line:84%
From any point of view,
something going faster

01:17:00.330 --> 01:17:03.140 align:middle line:84%
than light could be looked
at as being everywhere

01:17:03.140 --> 01:17:06.160 align:middle line:90%
at once, frozen in time.

01:17:06.160 --> 01:17:08.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so how
that applies to us,

01:17:08.790 --> 01:17:10.500 align:middle line:84%
I mean, bring this
all together for us.

01:17:10.500 --> 01:17:12.390 align:middle line:90%
How does this apply to our--

01:17:12.390 --> 01:17:14.920 align:middle line:84%
>>WOLF: Well, what
we're saying here

01:17:14.920 --> 01:17:17.530 align:middle line:84%
is that the universe
gets created

01:17:17.530 --> 01:17:26.210 align:middle line:84%
in which light going
forward in time

01:17:26.210 --> 01:17:30.370 align:middle line:84%
